	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.42.2; Fast. Cap. ([- -] Mugillan(us)); Chr. 354 (Capitolino et Mugilliano); Degrassi 26f., 96, 374f." ;
	dprr:hasID 402 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/401> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #401" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Antonius is a plebeian name, as Niebuhr saw (RG 2.480), but Livy (5.12.11-12) asserts that the first plebeian Mil. Tr. c. p. was elected in 400. Cf. Mommsen, RF 1.95. Papirius was probably a son of the Consul of 443 and himself the Censor of 418, hence the filiation L. f." ;
	dprr:hasID 401 .
